				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">AFAIK, when controller isn't plugged in it will read as all zeroes (this makes sense, so that running programs wouldn't think buttons are pressed down when the controller is unplugged). When an official Nintendo controller is plugged in, it will returns 1's after the first 8 reads. So you could test the result of 9th read, if it's 0, there's no controller. But IIRC some of the 3rd party controllers return 0's after the 8 reads, so this method would detect them as unplugged.. which is baaad. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /></div>

