				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I don't know what exactly you need to detect this for, but "for safety" you could add some extra checks, so that if 9th bit is 0, but any of the 1st-8th bit are non-zero (user is pressing buttons), set a flag to ignore the controller detection.
<br />
<br />So let's say you want to pause the game when no controller is detected. This way it would only pause it at the beginning of the game/whatever, and after user pressed START, it would work fine after that (with controller detection disabled).
<br />
<br />This could be detected seamlessly in a menu. However it wouldn't work perfectly if user decided to switch to a different controller after the fact. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /> But it wouldn't break the game either. And of course it would be possible to check it while the game is running too... I just don't feel like it's a very important feature since I don't ever remember the controllers coming loose by accident.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
